  "body": "Follow-up related to https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/pull/15036\r\n\r\n## ISSUE 1: The ring surrounding the avatar is not shown inside opened chat if a user didn't set the profile image\r\n#### Steps to reproduce:\r\n1. Don't set ENS for users\r\n2. Don't set images for the profiles of the users\r\n3. Send a message in any chat\r\n\r\n#### Actual result:\r\nThe ring is not shown for the user avatar on the opened chat if the profile image is not added\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52490791/223117543-50beca8e-8cfe-4848-8fb8-ed52dc269f81.png)\r\n\r\n#### Expected result:\r\nThe ring is shown inside the chat if the user didn't set the image for the profile\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52490791/223123841-6579065d-3d0b-4fd4-9dca-0d2f059c4546.png)\r\n\r\n#### Additional info:\r\n1. Current logic should work for such places where the user's avatar is shown:\r\n  - Profile page \r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52490791/223126973-630c8c51-5d60-49a6-823d-dc67e8f21b32.png)\r\n  - Contacts adding page\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52490791/223127563-5244f9d7-2c09-4102-b5df-603bec9cb8da.png)\r\n\r\n2. Current ring should be shown if the user has:\r\n  - Nickname (able to be set in the mobile app)\r\n  - Name (able to be set on desktop)\r\n  - 3 random name\r\n\r\n## ISSUE 2: The ring should not be shown in the chats and profile page if the user is with the ENS name and with set profile image\r\n#### Preconditions:\r\n1. User_A with ENS name\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce:\r\n1. log in as a user with a set ENS name (you can use the following user with ENS <volodymyr.eth>. Can be recovered with this seed phrase: spike spoil hidden sad juice force trap bind situate consider suit demand)\r\n2. Set the image into the profile\r\n3. Send a message into 1-1 chat\r\n4. Check the following pages:\r\n- Profile page\r\n- Avatar inside the opened chat\r\n\r\n5. As User_B: Check chat avatar (shown for user receiver of the message)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual result:\r\nThe ring is shown surrounding the user's avatar if the current user is with ens and with the set profile image on the following places:\r\n- Profile page\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52490791/223160119-cee96f56-fad8-4c28-9d16-36010a3cb1de.png)\r\n\r\n- Chat avatar\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52490791/223164568-0d26baf9-74d9-46a2-bcf5-a3c9c5b088cf.png)\r\n\r\n- Avatar inside the chat:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52490791/223165253-73938881-95d0-4adc-9d77-4a74d2c733fc.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected result:\r\nThe ring is not shown surrounding the user's avatar if the current user is with ens (no matter if an image is set or not for current user profile)\r\n",
